---
import Layout from '../layouts/Landing.astro';
---

<Layout title="contact wraith — team evaluation and support" description="Contact Wraith at info@wraith.cx for team evaluation, beta access, security questions, or support with recorded-traffic API mocking.">
  <section class="content-page">
    <div class="content-shell">
      <div class="eyebrow">contact</div>
      <h1>Evaluating Wraith for a team?</h1>
      <p class="lead">Use this path when you need help deciding whether Wraith fits your API mocking, CI, demo, or agent-environment workflow.</p>

      <h2>Best first message</h2>
      <ul class="note-list">
        <li><strong>Your current alternative</strong> WireMock, Mockoon, Postman, hand-written stubs, sandbox APIs, Speedscale, or something else.</li>
        <li><strong>The API you need to twin</strong> Protocol, auth shape, streaming needs, and whether this is for CI, local dev, demos, or agents.</li>
        <li><strong>The evaluation trigger</strong> Flaky tests, paid API usage, rate limits, demo reliability, sandbox state, or agent environment quality.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact route</h2>
      <p>Email <a href="mailto:info@wraith.cx">info@wraith.cx</a>. For release provenance, public install questions, or reproducible bugs, you can also use the <a href="https://github.com/bobisme/wraith-releases">release repository</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
